726997f-c.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 75th Street
726997f-c.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, opposite 75th Street (formerly Eads
Ave.), showing Denter Park Hotel; which is east of the Truants
Home that stands on the site of the former J. II. Snediker hotel.
Owners of the Denter Park Hotel were H. Woodruff, 1860: J. Hillegar,
1891; one Lypack, 1896; and also one Hasenflug. Hiram Woodruff's
first roadhouse was on Stony Road at the north side of Jamaica Ave.,
where Jewish Cemetery is now. This is a set of three views. View
No. 2 also shows the Murphy house on the right.
1922.
Views 2 \& 3: April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726998f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 75th Street
726998f-b.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 75th and 76th Streets, showing
in a set of three views showing Murphy's house and blacksmith shop,
which was established in 1835. It was here that many a famous horse,
running on the Union Course Race Track was shod.
1922.
Views 2 \& 3: April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
